OL,3,CScottish trade union confirms that
OL,4,Cstrikes will not take place this week
OL,6,FScottish trade union, Unite, has
OL,7,Fconfirmed that planned strikes for
OL,8,Flater this week have been suspended.
OL,10,FServices to waste and cleansing were
OL,11,Fset to be disrupted with bin strikes
OL,12,Fplanned across 18 councils, including
OL,13,Fin Dumfries and Galloway.
OL,15,FThe strikes were due to begin on
OL,16,FWednesday 14 August and the union has
OL,17,Fconfirmed that a ballot will now
OL,18,Fcommence amongst their members on a
OL,19,Fnew pay offer made by COSLA, the
OL,20,Forganisation which is the voice for
OL,21,Fthe councils in the country.
