OL,3,CScottish trade union confirms that
OL,4,Cstrikes will not take place this week
OL,6,F"Unite will now suspend the eight days
OL,7,Fof strike action so a ballot can take
OL,8,Fplace on the new offer."
OL,10,FUNISON Scotland local government lead
OL,11,FDavid O'Connor said: "UNISON has
OL,12,Fsuspended recycling and street
OL,13,Fcleansing strikes while staff are
OL,14,Fconsulted on COSLA's latest offer.
OL,16,F"UNISON's view is that it's still not
OL,17,Fenough. Council staff have seen the
OL,18,Fvalue of their pay reduced by 25% over
OL,19,Fthe past 14 years and any pay deal
OL,20,Fneeds to do more to reverse this."
